# Keep docker build context small + safe.
#
# Applies to all Dockerfiles that build with context = repo root
# (api, web, ai-worker). Without this, `docker build` uploads the entire
# ~1GB repo (node_modules, .git, .turbo cache, .env secrets) to the daemon,
# slowing builds and risking .env leakage into image layers.

# ── Dependencies / caches ────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.pnpm-store/
.turbo/
**/.turbo/
dist/
**/dist/
build/
**/build/
coverage/
**/coverage/
.pytest_cache/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ── Version control ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore

# ── Secrets & local env ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/.env.production

# ── IDE / editor ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# ── CI / docs (not needed at runtime) ────────────────────────────────────
.github/
docs/
*.md
!README.md
!apps/ai-worker/README.md

# ── Test fixtures / mocks that balloon the context ───────────────────────
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/test/
**/tests/
**/__tests__/
**/__mocks__/
**/test-fixtures/

# ── Railway / deployment configs (not needed in image) ───────────────────
railway.toml
**/railway.toml

# ── Temporary / log files ────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
tmp/
temp/

# ── Docker files themselves (except the one building) ────────────────────
# (Docker automatically ignores the Dockerfile being used; we don't need
# to ignore them here.)
